cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on training visual classifiers for stability prediction and utilising visual perception for object stacking. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of physical intuition for intelligent agents to perform complex tasks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the learning and utilisation of physical intuition by intelligent agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper involves training classifiers and leveraging learned physical intuition for active object stacking. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the stability of physical systems and the control of object stacking.
